At 06:00 AM 5/6/2002, Greg Thompson wrote:
>After spending mucho $$$ on complete front end rebuild, the front end is 
>nice and tight!....as a matter of fact, it's TOO tight....after turning a 
>corner, the steering wheel does not return to normal forward position 
>easily.  What could be causing this?  Is the whole front end just too 
>tight?  The mechanic and I have adjusted the steering box in both 
>directions with no effect.

The steering box adjustment screw is causing it.  If it's adjusted too 
tightly, it will "drag" going through the center position and cause the 
behavior you describe.  I doubt that it's good for the steering box either 
(I leave mine a little on the loose side just in case).

